      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STORMS WILL ROLL (1) boxed on well to finish third last time, beaten 2 lengths (17.63) behind CAWBOURNE LEOTA at this track. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Good form should continue. CAWBOURNE LEOTA (5) has a strong record here with 12 wins and seven placings from 21 starts. In the money last time at Bulli (19.49) in a Grade 5, finishing a 2.25 lengths third. Can feature in the finish. JUST A MONARCH (2) goes very well this course and distance starting 25 times for 10 wins and nine minors. Recorded a nose win (18.21) in a Grade 5 last time at Richmond. Looks suited here and can measure up. TINO BANNER (4) hit the frame latest (22.90) when third at Maitland in a Grade 5. Already a winner from this draw.",
